President Joe Biden has announced his intent to nominate Michael G. Whitaker as the Administrator of the Federal Aviation Administration (FAA). Whitaker currently serves as the chief operating officer of Supernal, a company within the Hyundai Motor Group that focuses on designing electric advanced air mobility vehicles. He previously served as the Deputy Administrator at the FAA from 2013 to 2016, where he played a key role in transitioning the nation's air traffic control system to satellite-enabled surveillance technology. Prior to his time at Supernal and the FAA, Whitaker served as the Group CEO of InterGlobe Enterprises, India's largest travel conglomerate, and spent 15 years at United Airlines in various roles. He has a juris doctorate degree from Georgetown University Law Center and is a private pilot. Whitaker also serves on the board of the Flight Safety Foundation, a nonprofit organization that promotes aviation safety globally.